8.01	Fort_Ruger	Fort Ruger	Fort Ruger is a fort on the island of Oahu that served as the first military reservation in the Territory of Hawaii. Named after Civil War General Thomas H. Ruger and built in and around Diamond Head Crater, the fort was established by the United States in 1909 for the purpose of defending the harbor of its newly annexed territory.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/USA_Hawaii_location_map.svg/240px-USA_Hawaii_location_map.svg.png
